quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  7,1,Alif L'am M'im Suad
  7,2,This Book is revealed to you; let there be no hesitation in your heart about it so that you may thereby warn the unbelievers and remind the believers
  7,3,"Say: \"O people, follow what has been brought down to you from your Lord and do not follow other patrons besides Him.\" Yet little do they take admonition"
  7,4,How many towns have We destroyed for their sins? Our scourge took them all of a sudden at night or while they were taking their afternoon rest
  7,5,"and when our scourge fell upon them, their only cry was: \"We have indeed been wrongdoers"
  7,6,On the Day of Judgment We shall question those to whom Messengers were sent and We shall also question the Messengers about Our message and its response
  7,7,Then We shall tell their whole story as an eye witness for We were never absent at any time or from any place
  7,8,"On that Day, the scale of justice shall be established. Those whose scale of good deeds will be heavy, they are the ones who will attain felicity"
  7,9,"and those whose scale is light, they shall find themselves in loss for they had done injustice to Our revelations"
  7,10,"We are the One Who established you on earth, and provided you means of your sustenance therein: yet little it is that you pay thanks"
  7,11,"Indeed We created you, then We fashioned you, then We asked the angels: \"Prostrate yourselves before Adam.\" They all prostrated accordingly except Iblees (Satan) who did not join those who prostrated"